&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is responsible for growing and engaging with Lucky Energy&#39;s online community while providing the insights that shape future content and creator strategies. They will own community management, social listening and performance reporting, while maintaining and evolving the Community Management Guide.&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;In short, this role focuses on community engagement, social listening and analytics across owned social and influencer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own day-to-day community management across social platforms, including comments, DMs and proactive engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with customer support to ensure seamless issue resolution and ensure quick response times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and expand the Community Management Guide, developing new response scenarios and ensuring consistent brand voice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct social listening through our 3rd party software to identify brand sentiment, emerging conversations and competitive insights to guide marketing team and content decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and regularly report on owned social, influencer and campaign performance across platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build monthly reporting decks, campaign recaps and performance dashboards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze content, creator and channel performance to identify trends and optimization opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surface key insights and recommendations to improve future content and influencer campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify standout creator content and top-performing creative for reposting, paid amplification and future inspiration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trend intelligence: Stay on the pulse of social media, internet culture, emerging conversations and platform trends to identify opportunities for Lucky to engage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regularly compile trending content formats, sounds, community behaviors and competitive insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively surface reactive marketing opportunities, social listening insights and content recommendations to the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-3 years of experience in community management, social media, digital marketing, social analytics, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing brand communities across platforms such as Instagram, TikTok, Facebook, LinkedIn, X, and YouTube.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of social media best practices, internet culture, platform trends, and community engagement strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using social listening and social media management tools to monitor conversations, sentiment, and competitor activity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills with experience creating performance reports, dashboards, and actionable recommendations from social and campaign data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written communication skills with the ability to adapt messaging while maintaining a consistent brand voice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple priorities, respond quickly in a fast-paced environment, and maintain attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience collaborating cross-functionally with marketing, customer support, creative teams, and agency partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and project management skills with the ability to manage ongoing reporting and community initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive, curious, and solutions-oriented, with a passion for building online communities and identifying opportunities to strengthen brand engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for social media, digital culture, consumer behavior, and turning insights into actionable marketing recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is responsible for building, organizing and optimizing Lucky Energy&#39;s owned social content and creator programs. They will partner closely with the Social Media Lead to develop content strategies, manage content pipelines and calendars, and support influencer campaigns from planning through execution. In short, focusing on content planning, creator strategy &amp;amp; influencer campaign management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain owned social content calendars&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize creative assets and maintain content libraries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source and pitch UGC creators to the internal team while managing timelines and content across multiple creators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate paid influencer partners based on brand fit, audience quality and campaign goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build creative briefs and content decks to guide agency partners and content creators to create brand-aligned content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with internal and external creative teams to help guide content development and execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research trends, creators and cultural moments to inspire content ideas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support influencer strategy, campaign planning and program organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage influencer gifting programs and campaign logistics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate creator campaigns, timelines and deliverables across agency and internal partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review creator content and identify opportunities for organic and paid amplification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trend intelligence: Stay on the pulse of social media, internet culture, creators, trending formats and cultural moments to inform owned content and influencer strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regularly compile trending content formats, creators, sounds and creative inspiration to bring fresh ideas to the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor competitor activity and best-in-class brands for content inspiration and strategic insights.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-4 years of experience in social media, influencer marketing, creator partnerships, digital marketing, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing social media content calendars and coordinating content across multiple platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of social media platforms, creator ecosystems, internet culture, and emerging digital trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience sourcing, evaluating, and managing influencer and UGC creator partnerships from outreach through content delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to develop creative briefs, organize content libraries, and manage multiple campaigns and deadlines simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong project management and organizational skills with exceptional attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience collaborating cross-functionally with internal teams, agencies, and external creators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical mindset with the ability to review campaign performance and identify opportunities for optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills with confidence providing creative feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter who thrives in a fast-paced, high-growth environment and is comfortable balancing strategy with hands-on execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for social media, content creation, influencer marketing, and staying ahead of cultural and platform trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Lucky Energy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lucky Energy is a fast-growing energy drink brand built on a simple belief: every day is a miracle. We&#39;re on a mission to bring bold flavor and good energy to every corner of the market, and we&#39;re building the team to do it! At Lucky, culture isn&#39;t an afterthought; it&#39;s how we work, how we grow, and how we win. If you&#39;re looking for a place where your impact is real and your energy is matched, you&#39;ve found it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director of Grocery is a senior commercial leader responsible for driving profitable growth across the grocery channel. You&#39;ll own the strategy, the relationships, and the results. This means managing broker partnerships, developing and closing national accounts, building joint business plans, and driving best-in-class retail execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll partner closely with our SVP of Sales and cross-functionally with Sales Planning, Marketing, Category Management, Finance, and Supply Chain, to deliver integrated channel strategies that scale. This is not a role for someone who delegates and disappears. This is a role for a hunter who has done startup life before: limited resources, maximum results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial Leadership &amp;amp; Customer Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Develop and execute national grocery strategy to deliver sales, profit, distribution, and market share objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain senior-level relationships with key grocery customers, wholesalers, and strategic partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead annual business planning, Joint Business Plans (JBPs), customer negotiations, and strategic growth initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to expand distribution, optimize assortment, and accelerate velocity across existing and emerging accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Finance to ensure profitable growth through effective pricing, trade investment, and promotional strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the voice of the customer internally, ensuring their needs are reflected in business decisions and growth plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Broker Network Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, structure, and manage Lucky Energy&#39;s broker network by recruiting the right partners, setting expectations, and holding them accountable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize broker performance by market; identify gaps and make swift decisions on partnerships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop broker incentive structures, communication cadences, and execution standards that drive consistent field results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Planning &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead customer planning processes including annual operating plans, promotional calendars, forecasting, and trade investment management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive best-in-class execution of new item launches, promotional programs, merchandising initiatives, and seasonal activations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor sales performance, market trends, and forecast accuracy to proactively identify risks and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Supply Chain and Demand Planning to optimize service levels, inventory, and customer fill rates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analytics &amp;amp; Insights&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage syndicated, retailer, and internal analytics to identify growth opportunities and inform strategic decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate data into actionable recommendations that improve account performance and strengthen category leadership&lt;/li&gt;
